-- ─── 4. Condition groups (nested + ALL/ANY) ─────────────────────────────────
DECLARE @bGroups NVARCHAR(MAX) = N'A WHEN tree is either ONE leaf condition OR a `group` node with a `logic` of "all" (AND) or "any" (OR) and a `children` array. Children may be more leaves OR nested groups (max depth 3 in the UI but the engine is unlimited).

Canonical shapes:

Single leaf (the simplest possible WHEN):
```json
{ "type":"rule", "field":"age", "operator":"gte", "value":"18" }
```

ALL (AND) — every child must be true:
```json
{
  "type":"group", "logic":"all",
  "children": [
    { "type":"rule", "field":"age",    "operator":"gte", "value":"18" },
    { "type":"rule", "field":"income", "operator":"gte", "value":"50000" }
  ]
}
```

ANY (OR) — at least one child true:
```json
{
  "type":"group", "logic":"any",
  "children": [
    { "type":"rule", "field":"country", "operator":"eq", "value":"US" },
    { "type":"rule", "field":"country", "operator":"eq", "value":"CA" }
  ]
}
```

NESTED — (age>=18 AND income>=50000) OR is_vip=true:
```json
{
  "type":"group", "logic":"any",
  "children": [
    {
      "type":"group", "logic":"all",
      "children": [
        { "type":"rule", "field":"age",    "operator":"gte", "value":"18" },
        { "type":"rule", "field":"income", "operator":"gte", "value":"50000" }
      ]
    },
    { "type":"rule", "field":"is_vip", "operator":"isTrue" }
  ]
}
```

Empty group: returns FALSE (defensive default — engine line 80). Don''t emit empty groups.

Negation: there is NO `not` group type. Use `neq` / `notIn` / `isEmpty` operators to negate at the leaf level. For NOT(group), invert the logic to "any/all" of negated leaves via De Morgan.';

